        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="TNYAdobeCaslonPro, 'Times New Roman', serif;" color="#000000">
          <h2 style="font-size:24px;line-height:1.2;font-weight:500;">EU indirectly compliant in Sudan</h2>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size:18px;line-height:1.5;"><strong>Summary: The investigation by France 24 shows that Europe, through an Emirati firm, diverts weapons to Sudan.</strong></p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">
          A FRANCE 24 investigation has uncovered that European-made weapons, despite an EU arms embargo, have reached Sudan‚Äôs conflict zones. The investigation points to the UAE‚Äôs International Golden Group (IGG), a private firm with a <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-22-04-2025-h3-4-history-of-diverting-weapons" target="_blank">history of diverting weapons</a> to embargoed areas such as Libya and Sudan. It also reveals secret connections between major European defense firms and IGG.
        </p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">Before being acquired by the state-owned Edge Group, IGG signed a series of partnerships with companies including Safran, Indra, and Leonardo. These partnerships have continued, despite reports from Amnesty International and the UN showing Emirati-supplied vehicles and French-made systems being used by Sudanese militias such as the Rapid Support Forces (RSF). These weapons have reportedly been used in attacks on civilians, resulting in significant casualties.</p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">The European companies involved claim to follow export laws, but concerns persist. Critics argue that these partnerships enable the spread of weapons in conflict zones. They also contend that such actions violate international embargoes and potentially link European firms to human rights abuses.</p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;"><i>Read the rest of France24's 5-part investigative series <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-22-04-2025-h3-5-here" target="_blank">here</a></i></p>
        </mj-text>
    </mj-section>
