          <p style="font-size:18px;line-height:1.5;">
            <strong>üáÆüá≥ JD Vance arrives in India for tough trade talks with Modi</strong>
          </p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">
           JD Vance‚Äôs largely personal visit to the country will involve meeting PM Modi as the government rushes to escape the sweeping tariffs. India is navigating carefully amid rising US-China trade tensions. PM Modi's government may cut tariffs on more than half of its $41.8B imports from the US to secure a trade agreement. Although President Trump referred to India as a ‚Äútariff king,‚Äù the two nations have strong ties.
          </p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">Vance‚Äôs <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-22-04-2025-br1-6-visit-to-india" target="_blank">visit to India</a> is seen as necessary groundwork before Trump‚Äôs expected visit for the Quad summit. While no agreements are likely to be made during Vance‚Äôs trip, talks on defense cooperation are moving forward. This includes plans to co-produce the Javelin missile and the Stryker vehicle. Discussions will continue during the upcoming visit by US Defense Secretary Pete Hegseth.</p>
        </mj-text>
