          <p style="font-size:18px;line-height:1.5;">
            <strong>üá®üá≥ Beijing warns countries against conspiring with the US to restrict trade</strong>
          </p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">As the US-China trade war escalates, other countries are unwillingly dragged in. China has warned that it will take <a style="text-decoration: none; border-bottom: 2px solid  #06266D; color: black;" href="https://link.geopoliticalsummary.com/gs-22-04-2025-br2-7-retaliatory-measures" target="_blank">retaliatory measures</a> against countries that support the United States in trade agreements that undermine Chinese interests. President Trump‚Äôs administration has set tariffs as high as 145% on Chinese imports. In comparison, other nations face a blanket 10% tariff and won‚Äôt have to struggle with the additional ones if they negotiate.</p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.5;">China is not entertaining the idea of negotiating. It has hit back with 125% tariffs on US goods. The US pressures its allies, such as Japan, South Korea, and India, to restrict trade with China in exchange for more tariff exemptions. Critics warn that the strategy risks destabilizing global markets and drawing other nations into the conflict, which they have no desire to participate.</p>
        </mj-text>
      </mj-column>
